This paper discusses unbiased Learning to Rank (LTR) methods, which are commonly used in information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (ML) applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also discusses the theoretical guarantees and empirical results of the two methodologies, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the effect of user experience during learning, which could place it in cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper discusses the applicability of the two methodologies, which could place it in cs.CY (Computers and Society).
